An 18-year-old student, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, carried out a shooting at Jokela High School in Tuusula, Finland, killing eight people before taking his own life.
This tragic event marked the first shooting at a Finnish school since 1989.
Auvinen, known for his radical beliefs, posted videos online praising past school shooters.
The incident shocked the nation, prompting condolences from Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen and flags flown at half-mast.
The victims, including the headmistress and students, were mourned as Finland grappled with the aftermath of this senseless act of violence.
